urls.description: Each year we observe Transgender Day of Remembrance (TDOR) to honour the memory of transgender people whose lives have been lost in acts of anti-trans violence, and due to discrimination and stigma. This commemorative event is presented by Transgender Victoria and Yarra Libraries, supported by The Ewing Trust, and co-presented in partnership with Drummond Street Services, Parents of Gender Diverse Children, Switchboard, The Shed, Trans Pride March Melbourne, Transcend, Queerspace & Zoe Belle Gender
